# aws-cli v2 installer GPG public key
#
# The toolbox Dockerfile verifies the aws-cli v2 installer's signature against
# this key (a real supply-chain check, not a checksum the same server serves).
# This is AWS's published aws-cli signing key, vendored here so the build is
# reproducible with no manual step. It is a PUBLIC key — safe to commit — but
# verify it yourself before trusting it: the fingerprint below must match the
# one AWS lists in "Verifying the integrity of your downloaded files".
#
#   pub  rsa4096/A6310ACC4672475C  AWS CLI Team <aws-cli@amazon.com>
#   fpr  FB5D B77F D5C1 18B8 0511  ADA8 A631 0ACC 4672 475C
#
# This key EXPIRES 2027-07-01 (refreshed 2026-07-07 — AWS extended the same
# key's self-signature; the fingerprint is unchanged). When it next expires,
# gpg --verify will warn/fail and the key must be refreshed — see the colocated
# awscli-public-key.asc.example for the fetch-and-verify procedure.
